    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cultural gathering practiced by Northwest Coast Native Americans that commemorates the lives of deceased clan members; historically has referred to any kind of potlach ceremony but in contemporary usage refers specifically to memorial services. Gift giving and speeches are a central feature of the event.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
